Miscellaneous Highlights: The Bucks never found themselves behind San Antonio on the scoreboard after an AJ Green three-pointer with 3:09 left in the first quarter.
The Spurs' second-year center Victor Wembanyama made just 4-of-10 field goal attempts, including 2-of-6 from three-point range.
Milwaukee's field goal percentage against San Antonio was 47.8, while San Antonio had a 36.8 field goal percentage.
The 16 point loss to the Bucks gave the Spurs their third-straight loss, leaving the Spurs as the Western Conference No. 10 seed.
Others: Giannis Antetokounmpo (34) dunks in front of San Antonio Spurs forward Victor Wembanyama (1) during the first quarter at Fiserv Forum.
